&lt;h2 id=&quot;the-tasks-ahead&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#the-tasks-ahead&quot; aria-label=&quot;the tasks ahead permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;The Tasks Ahead&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Tasks Ahead&lt;/strong&gt; is a much more simplistic subsection. I keep an extremely simple to-do list, consisting of three columns: &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;Backlog&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;Doing&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;Done&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
      style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;&quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
    style=&quot;padding-bottom: 34.106280193236714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
  &gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        alt=&quot;My To-Do List&quot;
        title=&quot;My To-Do List&quot;
        src=&quot;/blog/static/abe3c67421b1851868d679ccfa448214/b9e4f/wiki-to-do.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/blog/static/abe3c67421b1851868d679ccfa448214/cf440/wiki-to-do.png 148w,
/blog/static/abe3c67421b1851868d679ccfa448214/d2d38/wiki-to-do.png 295w,
/blog/static/abe3c67421b1851868d679ccfa448214/b9e4f/wiki-to-do.png 590w,
/blog/static/abe3c67421b1851868d679ccfa448214/f9b6a/wiki-to-do.png 885w,
/blog/static/abe3c67421b1851868d679ccfa448214/17fa4/wiki-to-do.png 1035w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
        loading=&quot;lazy&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;Backlog&lt;/code&gt; is where I typically throw items I want to look into within the next few weeks, but aren‚Äôt a pressing priority. &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;Doing&lt;/code&gt; is where the higher priority items typically land, things I believe I can accomplish that day or week. &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;Done&lt;/code&gt; only exists as a point of pride; it‚Äôs nice to see all those checked-off items populating the far right column at the end of a long week. I always end up deleting the completed tasks (I used to maintain an Archive, but I never went back in ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è), but it‚Äôs nice to bask in your accomplishments for a day or two beforehand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;in-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#in-conclusion&quot; aria-label=&quot;in conclusion permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;In Conclusion&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Between these two subsections, I manage to track most of the things I need to do in my personal life within a week. üéâ Hopefully you can get some use out of a similar approach, using my templates, to which I have linked below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;templates&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#templates&quot; aria-label=&quot;templates permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Templates&lt;/h2&gt;
